431
00:30:22,796 --> 00:30:27,009
我們想也許…，如果我們能搞清楚 他最後的話是什麼意思…
We thought maybe.... If we could find out what he meant by his last words...

432
00:30:27,092 --> 00:30:29,636
…他臨終時說的話 - 是那句“玫瑰花蕾”嗎？
-...as he was dying. -That "Rosebud"?

433
00:30:29,678 --> 00:30:32,180
也許是某一個姑娘？
Maybe some girl?

434
00:30:32,264 --> 00:30:34,516
在他早期生活中有不少
There were a lot of them in the early days.

435
00:30:34,558 --> 00:30:37,811
不大可能吧 凱恩先生以前和一個姑娘萍水相逢…
It's hardly likely that Mr. Kane could have met someone casually...

436
00:30:37,853 --> 00:30:40,147
而五十年後，在他臨終時…
...and then 50 years later, on his deathbed--

437
00:30:40,188 --> 00:30:45,027
你還太年輕，湯…湯姆遜先生
Well, you're pretty young, Mr. Thompson.

438
00:30:45,193 --> 00:30:48,822
一個人可能記得許多 你認為他不會記得的東西
A fellow will remember a lot of things you wouldn't think he'd remember.

439
00:30:48,905 --> 00:30:50,657
你相信我的話
You take me.

440
00:30:50,699 --> 00:30:55,787
有一天，早在1896年 我正乘渡船到澤西去
One day, back in 1896, I was crossing over to Jersey on the ferry...

441
00:30:55,996 --> 00:30:59,207
船離開碼頭時，另一條渡船正要靠碼頭
...and as we pulled out, there was another ferry pulling in...

442
00:30:59,249 --> 00:31:02,044
船上站著一個姑娘等著下船
...and on it there was a girl waiting to get off.

443
00:31:02,878 --> 00:31:04,671
她穿著一件白色衣裙
A white dress she had on.

444
00:31:04,713 --> 00:31:07,215
手堮陬菑@把白陽傘
She was carrying a white parasol.

445
00:31:07,549 --> 00:31:10,010
我看她只有一眨眼的工夫
I only saw her for one second.

446
00:31:10,093 --> 00:31:15,557
而她根本沒有看見我 我打賭，從那以後沒有哪一個月…
She didn't see me at all, but I'll bet a month hasn't gone by since...

447
00:31:16,433 --> 00:31:19,019
我沒有想著她
...that I haven't thought of that girl.

448
00:31:19,519 --> 00:31:23,732
- 你都見到過哪些人？ - 噢，我到過亞特蘭大城
-Who else have you been to see? -Well, I went down to Atlantic City.

449
00:31:23,774 --> 00:31:25,734
蘇珊？
Susie?

450
00:31:25,859 --> 00:31:27,194
謝謝
Thank you.

451
00:31:27,736 --> 00:31:30,614
他去世的那天，我給她打了個電話
I called her myself the day after he died.

452
00:31:30,947 --> 00:31:33,367
我覺得，總該有人…
I thought maybe somebody ought to.

453
00:31:34,660 --> 00:31:38,955
- 她甚至不能來接電話 - 過兩天我還要再去看她
-She couldn't even come to the phone. -I?l be seeing her again in a couple of days.

454
00:31:39,039 --> 00:31:41,041
關於玫瑰花蕾，伯恩斯坦先生
About Rosebud, Mr. Bernstein.

455
00:31:41,249 --> 00:31:44,878
您能否就您記憶所及隨便談談 有關凱恩先生的任何事
If you'd talk about anything connected with Mr. Kane that you can remember.

456
00:31:44,962 --> 00:31:46,922
您一開始就和他在一起的
You were with him from the beginning.

457
00:31:46,964 --> 00:31:52,386
在開始之前，年輕人 現在是在他死之後（假惺惺）
From before the beginning, young fellow. And now it's after the end.

458
00:31:53,428 --> 00:31:55,764
除了蘇珊之外，你還試著找過別人嗎？
Have you tried to see anybody except Susie?

459
00:31:55,847 --> 00:32:00,185
我尚未見過其他任何人 不過我已去過華爾特·賽切爾紀念館
I haven't seen anybody else, but I've been through Walter Thatcher's journal.

460
00:32:00,268 --> 00:32:04,731
- 賽切爾！那個人是我遇見過的最大的蠢貨 - 可他發了大財
-That man was the biggest fool I ever met. -He made an awful lot of money.

461
00:32:04,815 --> 00:32:07,609
發財不需要什麼本事
Well, it's no trick to make a lot of money...

462
00:32:08,110 --> 00:32:13,365
…如果你一心只是想發財
...if all you want is to make a lot of money.

463
00:32:15,951 --> 00:32:21,289
就拿凱恩先生來說，他要的就不是錢
You take Mr. Kane. It wasn't money he wanted.

464
00:32:23,500 --> 00:32:27,713
賽切爾先生從來沒能把他捉摸透 有時，甚至連我也辦不到
Thatcher never did figure him out. Sometimes even I couldn't.

465
00:32:27,879 --> 00:32:31,300
你知道你該找誰談嗎？ 傑德·李蘭先生
You know who you ought to see? Mr. Leland.

466
00:32:31,466 --> 00:32:34,553
他是凱恩先生生前密友 他們一道上學的
He was Mr. Kane's closest friend. They went to school together.

467
00:32:34,636 --> 00:32:35,804
哈佛大學嗎？
Harvard?

468
00:32:35,887 --> 00:32:39,558
哈佛，耶魯，康奈爾，普林斯頓，瑞士
Oh, Harvard, Yale, Princeton, Cornell, Switzerland.

469
00:32:39,641 --> 00:32:42,269
他被許多大學除名
He was thrown out of a lot of colleges.

470
00:32:42,477 --> 00:32:45,105
李蘭先生從來都是一文不名
Mr. Leland never had a nickel.

471
00:32:45,439 --> 00:32:48,442
那種老家族，父親稱其有一千萬
One of those families where the father is worth $10 million...

472
00:32:48,525 --> 00:32:52,821
可有朝一日他開槍自殺了 結果查明他除了一身債，什麼也沒有
...then one day he shoots himself, and it turns out there's nothing but debts.

473
00:32:54,489 --> 00:32:56,742
凱恩先生第一天接管《問事報》報社時他和我都在場…
He was with Mr. Kane and me...

474
00:32:57,743 --> 00:33:00,662
凱恩先生第一天接管《問事報》報社時他和我都在場…
...the first day Mr. Kane took over the Inquirer.

475
00:33:08,337 --> 00:33:10,839
瞧一瞧，傑德
Take a good look at it, Jedediah.

476
00:33:11,089 --> 00:33:14,968
過些日子它將要大大改觀
It's going to look a lot different one of these days. Come on.

477
00:33:23,727 --> 00:33:27,022
這座樓堥S有臥室，這是一家報社大樓
There ain't no bedrooms in this joint. That's a newspaper building.

478
00:33:27,105 --> 00:33:31,902
雇你來是發表意見的，還是拉東西的？
You're getting paid, mister, for opinions or for hauling?

479
00:33:34,696 --> 00:33:37,616
- 傑德 - 你先請，凱恩先生
-Jedediah. -After you, Mr. Kane.

480
00:33:49,836 --> 00:33:52,047
對不起，先生，我…
Excuse me, sir, but l....

481
00:33:55,008 --> 00:33:57,386
歡迎，凱恩先生
Welcome, Mr. Kane.

482
00:33:59,471 --> 00:34:02,224
歡迎到《問事報》報社來，凱恩先生
Welcome to the Inquirer, Mr. Kane.

483
00:34:02,265 --> 00:34:04,559
我是赫伯特·卡特，報紙的主編
I am Herbert Carter, the editor-in-chief.

484
00:34:04,643 --> 00:34:08,563
- 謝謝你，卡特先生，這位是李蘭先生 - 您好，李蘭先生！
-Thank you, Mr. Carter. This is Mr. Leland-- -How do you do, Mr. Leland?

485
00:34:08,605 --> 00:34:11,566
李蘭先生是新來的戲劇評論家 希望我沒說錯
Our new dramatic critic. I hope I haven't made a mistake.

486
00:34:11,608 --> 00:34:13,860
- 戲劇評論家，對嗎？ - 是的
-It is dramatic critic, right? -That's right.

487
00:34:13,902 --> 00:34:17,531
- 他們是為我起立的嗎？ - 你？噢，凱恩先生
-Are they standing for me? -You? Oh, Mr. Kane.

488
00:34:18,031 --> 00:34:18,907
起立？
Standing?

489
00:34:18,949 --> 00:34:20,575
- 你好 - 你好
-How do you do? -How do you do?

490
00:34:20,659 --> 00:34:23,036
我覺得這是一個善意的表示
I thought it would be a nice little gesture.

491
00:34:23,078 --> 00:34:26,206
- 請他們坐下，請坐下 - 對新的辦報人
-Ask them to sit down, will you, please. -The new publisher.

492
00:34:26,790 --> 00:34:30,669
- 你們可以恢復工作了，先生們 - 謝謝
-You may resume your duties, gentlemen. -Thank you.

493
00:34:30,752 --> 00:34:34,089
- 我不瞭解您的計畫 - 我也不知道我的計畫
-l didn't know your plans. -l don't know my plans myself.

494
00:34:34,423 --> 00:34:36,758
- 說實在的，我沒有任何計畫 - 沒有？
-Matter of fact, I haven't got any plans. -No?

495
00:34:36,800 --> 00:34:39,845
就是要辦一份報
Except to get out a newspaper.

496
00:34:44,099 --> 00:34:46,435
- 伯恩斯坦先生！ - 是的，凱恩先生
-Mr. Bernstein. -Yes, Mr. Kane.

497
00:34:46,518 --> 00:34:48,895
卡特先生，這是伯恩斯坦先生
Mr. Carter, this is Mr. Bernstein.

498
00:34:48,979 --> 00:34:53,984
- 伯恩斯坦先生是我的總經理 - 你好，卡特先生
-Mr. Bernstein is my general manager. -How do you do, Mr. Carter?

499
00:34:54,067 --> 00:34:55,944
- 卡特先生 - 你好
-Mr. Carter. -How do you do?

500
00:34:56,945 --> 00:34:59,281
- 您好，伯恩斯坦先生！ - Stein
-Yes, Mr. Bernstein. -Stein.

501
00:34:59,364 --> 00:35:03,035
- 凱恩 - 卡特先生，這是你的辦公室？
-Kane. -Mr. Carter, is this your office?

502
00:35:03,118 --> 00:35:07,247
我那小小的私室可供閣下使用
My little private sanctum is at your disposal.

503
00:35:07,331 --> 00:35:10,751
- 讓一下 - 不過我不明白…
-Excuse me. -But I don't think I understand.

504
00:35:11,126 --> 00:35:15,130
卡特先生，我以後就住在這兒 住多久看工作需要再說
Mr. Carter, I'm going to live right here in your office as long as I have to.

505
00:35:16,256 --> 00:35:18,216
住在這兒？是嗎？
Live here? Yes?

506
00:35:18,300 --> 00:35:21,261
- 讓一下 - 但是一家晨報，畢竟…
-Excuse me. -But a morning newspaper, after all--

507
00:35:21,345 --> 00:35:22,179
讓一下
Excuse me.

508
00:35:22,262 --> 00:35:26,141
我們一天有十二個小時是關閉的
We're practically closed for 12 hours a day.

509
00:35:26,433 --> 00:35:29,561
這是我認為需要改變的一件事
That's one of the things that's going to have to be changed here.

510
00:35:29,645 --> 00:35:33,190
- 新聞是一天二十四小時都有的 - 二十四小時？
-The news goes on for 24 hours a day. -24?

511
00:35:33,315 --> 00:35:36,652
- 是的 - 讓一下
-That's right. -Excuse me.

512
00:35:36,735 --> 00:35:38,445
怎麼可能…
It's impossible....

513
00:35:38,487 --> 00:35:43,533
我畫好了卡通 我對漫畫不在行
I've drawn that cartoon. I'm no good as a cartoonist.

514
00:35:43,617 --> 00:35:45,202
你當然不是
You certainly aren't.

515
00:35:45,285 --> 00:35:47,120
你是戲劇評論家，李蘭
You're the dramatic critic, Leland.

516
00:35:47,162 --> 00:35:49,164
- 你還在吃呢？ - 我沒吃飽呢！
-You still eating? -I? still hungry.

517
00:35:49,206 --> 00:35:51,708
我不是批評你，卡特先生 《紀實報》上有一個頭版故事
Here's a front-page story in the Chronicle...

518
00:35:51,792 --> 00:35:54,920
布魯克林區一位叫西佛爾斯東的婦女失蹤了
...about a Mrs. Harry Silverstone in Brooklyn who's missing.

519
00:35:55,003 --> 00:35:59,633
她可能是被謀殺了 為什麼《問事報》今天早上沒有登？
She's probably murdered. Why isn't there something about it in the Inquirer?

520
00:35:59,675 --> 00:36:01,510
我們辦的是新聞報…
We're running a newspaper...

521
00:36:01,551 --> 00:36:04,513
- 傑德，我都快餓昏了 -…而不是什麼醜聞小報
-I? absolutely starving to death. -...not a scandal sheet.

522
00:36:05,389 --> 00:36:06,640
好的
That's all right.

523
00:36:06,682 --> 00:36:10,686
卡特先生，《紀實報》用了三欄標題
Mr. Carter, here is a three-column headline in the Chronicle.

524
00:36:10,769 --> 00:36:13,313
為什麼我們沒有用？
Why hasn't the Inquirer a three-column headline?

525
00:36:13,397 --> 00:36:14,856
這件新聞不夠大
The news wasn't big enough.

526
00:36:14,940 --> 00:36:19,695
卡特先生，只要標題夠大 也就能使新聞夠大
Mr. Carter, if the headline is big enough, it makes the news big enough.

527
00:36:19,736 --> 00:36:22,364
- 就是！ - 關於西佛爾斯東太太被謀殺…
-That's right! -The murder of Mrs. Harry Silverstone--

528
00:36:22,447 --> 00:36:24,658
沒有事實證明這個女人是被謀害了 甚至不能證明她已死了
There's no proof that she was murdered, or dead.

529
00:36:24,700 --> 00:36:27,577
《紀實報》說她失蹤了，鄰居們開始懷疑
It says she's missing. The neighbors are getting suspicious.

530
00:36:27,661 --> 00:36:30,539
我們的職責不是報導家庭婦女的閒話
It's not our function to report the gossip of housewives.

531
00:36:30,622 --> 00:36:34,876
如果我們對這類事發生興趣 我們的報紙的內容每天可多一倍
If we were interested in that kind of thing, we could fill the paper twice over, daily.

532
00:36:34,918 --> 00:36:38,297
從今天起我們就要對這類東西發生興趣了 卡特先生
That's the kind of thing we are going to be interested in from now on.

533
00:36:38,380 --> 00:36:41,341
我希望你派一名最精幹的人 去找西佛爾斯東先生
I want you to send your best man to see Mr. Silverstone.

534
00:36:41,425 --> 00:36:45,304
讓他跟西佛爾斯東先生說， 如果他不立即交出他的妻子…
Have him tell Mr. Silverstone if he doesn't produce his wife, Mrs. Silverstone...

535
00:36:45,387 --> 00:36:47,472
…《問事報》就要設法使他進牢房
...the Inquirer will have him arrested.

536
00:36:47,556 --> 00:36:50,017
叫他告訴西佛爾斯東 說他是一名偵探…
Tell Mr. Silverstone he's a detective from....

537
00:36:50,100 --> 00:36:52,561
- 隸屬於中央署 - 中央署
-Central Office. -The Central Office.

538
00:36:52,894 --> 00:36:57,399
如果西佛爾斯東先生起了疑心 要看他的證章
If Mr. Silverstone gets suspicious and asks to see your man's badge...

539
00:36:57,482 --> 00:37:01,320
你的人就裝出憤慨的樣子 把西佛爾斯東先生叫作無政府主義者
...your man is to get indignant and call Mr. Silverstone an anarchist.

540
00:37:01,570 --> 00:37:04,781
要大聲地喊，讓左右鄰居都能聽到 你想吃飯嗎，傑德？
Loudly, so the neighbors can hear. You ready for dinner, Jedediah?

541
00:37:04,865 --> 00:37:08,118
凱恩先生，我沒法相信 一家受人尊重的報紙的職責…
I can't see that the function of a respectable newspaper--

542
00:37:08,243 --> 00:37:11,371
卡特先生，你是最能領會的，再見
Thank you so much, Mr. Carter. Goodbye.

543
00:37:11,955 --> 00:37:13,206
再見
Goodbye.

544
00:37:13,915 --> 00:37:16,752
報紙！快來看！
Paper! Read all about it!

545
00:37:17,002 --> 00:37:19,921
快來看今早出版的《紀實報》
Read all about it in the early morning Chronicle.

546
00:37:20,005 --> 00:37:22,466
布魯克林女士消失之謎
The mystery of the lady that vanished in Brooklyn.

547
00:37:23,884 --> 00:37:26,386
快來看今早出版的《紀實報》
Read all about it in the early morning Chronicle.

548
00:37:40,067 --> 00:37:43,695
我們的報紙就要上街了，查利，再過十分鐘
We'll be on the street soon, Charlie, another 10 minutes.

549
00:37:43,820 --> 00:37:46,531
晚了三小時五十分，不過我們已完成了
Three hours and 50 minutes late, but we did it.

550
00:37:46,615 --> 00:37:48,158
- 累了嗎？ - 這一天可真夠瞧的
-Tired? -A tough day.

551
00:37:48,241 --> 00:37:49,868
- 浪費掉的一天 - 浪費掉的？
-A wasted day. -Wasted?

552
00:37:49,951 --> 00:37:52,871
你今晚改了四次版，就是這麼回事
You only made the paper over four times tonight, that's all.

553
00:37:53,121 --> 00:37:56,583
我把頭版稍稍改了一下，伯恩斯坦先生 這不夠
I've changed the front page a little, Mr. Bernstein. That's not enough.

554
00:37:56,625 --> 00:38:00,879
除了照片和文字以外 我還要給這份報搞點兒什麼東西
There's something I've got to get into this paper besides pictures and print.

555
00:38:01,463 --> 00:38:04,591
我要讓《問事報》對紐約的重要性就象
I've got to make the New York Inquirer as important to New York...

556
00:38:04,633 --> 00:38:06,551
…點燃那個燈的煤氣一樣重要
...as the gas in that light.

557
00:38:07,177 --> 00:38:08,971
那你想怎麼辦呢，查利？
What are you going to do, Charlie?

558
00:38:09,054 --> 00:38:13,225
我的原則宣言，別笑，傑德
My Declaration of Principles. Don't smile, Jedediah.

559
00:38:13,642 --> 00:38:16,103
我已經把它寫在這
I've got it all written out here.

560
00:38:16,645 --> 00:38:19,690
你千萬別作出你不準備履行的諾言
You don't want to make any promises you don't want to keep.

561
00:38:19,773 --> 00:38:21,441
這些是要履行的
These'll be kept.

562
00:38:22,317 --> 00:38:24,820
我要向本市居民提供一份…
"I?l provide the people of this city...

563
00:38:25,153 --> 00:38:28,740
…日報，它要忠實地報導新聞
"...with a daily paper that will tell all the news honestly.

564
00:38:29,992 --> 00:38:33,328
-“我還要向他們提供…” - 這是第二句你用“我”來開始的
-"l will also provide--" -That's two sentences starting with "l."

565
00:38:33,412 --> 00:38:35,998
人們該知道是誰在負責
People will know who's responsible...

566
00:38:36,081 --> 00:38:40,127
“他們會從《問事報》中得到真實的新聞 快速、簡單而又有趣味”
...and they'll get the truth in the Inquirer, quickly, simply and entertainingly.

567
00:38:40,210 --> 00:38:43,588
“不允許有任何特殊利益來乾預這些新聞”
No special interests will be allowed to interfere with that truth.

568
00:38:43,672 --> 00:38:47,551
“我還將向他們提供一個 為市民和人的權利而進行…”
"l will also provide them with a fighting and tireless champion of their rights...

569
00:38:47,634 --> 00:38:50,262
“不倦鬥爭的鬥士”
