716
00:48:28,840 --> 00:48:32,219
凱恩先生這個人，幾乎失去了所有的一切
Mr. Kane was a man who lost almost everything he had.

717
00:48:32,886 --> 00:48:35,138
你該和傑德·李蘭先生談談
You ought to see Jed Leland.

718
00:48:35,222 --> 00:48:38,392
當然，他和凱恩先生並非完全志同道合
Of course, he and Mr. Kane didn't exactly see eye to eye.

719
00:48:38,475 --> 00:48:40,477
就拿西美戰爭來說吧
You take the Spanish-American war.

720
00:48:40,560 --> 00:48:43,939
我看李蘭先生是對的，那是凱恩先生的戰爭
I guess Mr. Leland was right. That was Mr. Kane's war.

721
00:48:43,981 --> 00:48:46,984
我們沒有什麼可為之而戰的
We didn't really have anything to fight about.

722
00:48:47,776 --> 00:48:51,363
不過，如果沒有凱恩先生的那場戰爭…
Do you think if it hadn't been for that war of Mr. Kane's...

723
00:48:51,655 --> 00:48:54,408
…你認為我們能得到巴拿馬運河嗎？
...we'd have the Panama Canal?

724
00:48:55,075 --> 00:48:57,577
但願我知道李蘭先生現在的下落
I wish I knew where Mr. Leland was.

725
00:48:58,161 --> 00:49:01,331
長時間以來他們不再告訴我這類事情
A lot of the time now they don't tell me these things.

726
00:49:02,624 --> 00:49:04,459
也許他已經死了
Maybe even he's dead.

727
00:49:04,584 --> 00:49:06,295
如果你想知道，伯恩斯坦先生
In case you'd like to know...

728
00:49:06,378 --> 00:49:09,339
他現在在第180號街的亨丁頓紀念醫院
...he's at the Huntington Memorial Hospital on 180th Street.

729
00:49:09,423 --> 00:49:10,924
真的嗎！我還以為…
You don't say. I had--

730
00:49:10,966 --> 00:49:13,885
他們說，他沒有什麼特殊的病，只不過…
Nothing particular the matter with him, they tell me, just....

731
00:49:13,969 --> 00:49:16,555
只不過是上了年紀
Just old age.

732
00:49:17,848 --> 00:49:22,769
湯姆遜先生，這是唯一一種 你沒有指望能治得好的病
It's the only disease that you don't look forward to being cured of.

733
00:49:34,865 --> 00:49:37,743
我什麼都記得，年青人
I can remember absolutely everything, young man.

734
00:49:37,826 --> 00:49:39,119
這是對我的詛咒
That's my curse.

735
00:49:39,161 --> 00:49:43,749
這是人類所遭受的最大的詛咒：記憶
That's one of the greatest curses ever inflicted on the human race: memory.

736
00:49:44,708 --> 00:49:49,546
我是他最老的朋友 就他跟我的關係來說，他的表現象豬玀
I was his oldest friend, and as far as I was concerned, he behaved like a swine.

737
00:49:49,796 --> 00:49:53,884
倒不是說查利生性粗暴 但是他做出了粗暴的事情
Not that Charlie was ever brutal. He just did brutal things.

738
00:49:54,676 --> 00:49:58,930
也許我不是他的朋友 如果我不是，那他就一個朋友也沒有
Maybe I wasn't his friend, but if I wasn't, he never had one.

739
00:49:59,181 --> 00:50:02,809
也許我就是你們今天叫作小丑的那種人
Maybe I was what you nowadays call a stooge.

740
00:50:02,851 --> 00:50:05,228
李蘭先生，你對玫瑰花蕾知道些什麼？
You were about to say something about Rosebud.

741
00:50:05,312 --> 00:50:07,522
你是否正巧帶著雪茄？
Do you happen to have a good cigar?

742
00:50:07,606 --> 00:50:11,485
給我看病的那個年輕醫生認為我該戒煙
I've got a young physician here who thinks I'm going to give up smoking.

743
00:50:11,526 --> 00:50:13,862
很抱歉，我沒有
No, I'm afraid I haven't. Sorry.

744
00:50:14,196 --> 00:50:15,864
我改變了話題，是嗎？
I changed the subject, didn't l?

745
00:50:15,947 --> 00:50:18,408
我成了一個多麼令人討嫌的老人啊
What a disagreeable old man I have become.

746
00:50:19,368 --> 00:50:24,206
你是記者，想知道我對查利·凱恩的看法
You're a reporter and you want to know what I think about Charlie Kane.

747
00:50:27,626 --> 00:50:30,170
我認為他有自己的偉大之處
I suppose he had some private sort of greatness.

748
00:50:30,212 --> 00:50:31,964
不過，他太自私
But he kept it to himself.

749
00:50:32,047 --> 00:50:35,008
他絕不會委屈自己 也不會捨棄任何東西
He never gave himself away. He never gave anything away.

750
00:50:35,050 --> 00:50:38,053
他只是給你點兒甜頭
He just left you a tip.

751
00:50:39,554 --> 00:50:40,931
他思路開闊
He had a generous mind.

752
00:50:41,014 --> 00:50:44,184
我看從來沒有人有他那樣多的主意
I don't suppose anybody ever had so many opinions.

753
00:50:44,476 --> 00:50:47,187
但是他除了查利·凱恩以外誰也不相信
But he never believed in anything except Charlie Kane.

754
00:50:47,270 --> 00:50:50,899
他一生除了查利·凱恩，什麼信仰也沒有
He never had a conviction except Charlie Kane in his life.

755
00:50:51,191 --> 00:50:53,402
我猜他到死也沒有
I suppose he died without one.

756
00:50:53,568 --> 00:50:56,154
那一定是很糟糕的
That must have been pretty unpleasant.

757
00:50:56,488 --> 00:51:01,159
當然，不少人離開這個世界時 對於死亡是沒有什麼信仰的
Of course, a lot of us check out without having any special convictions about death.

758
00:51:01,243 --> 00:51:04,496
但是我們知道自己留下了什麼 我們有某種信仰
But we do know what we're leaving. We do believe in something.

759
00:51:05,163 --> 00:51:08,208
你肯定身邊沒帶雪茄嗎？
Are you absolutely sure you haven't got a cigar?

760
00:51:08,375 --> 00:51:10,377
- 很遺憾，李蘭先生 - 沒關係
-Sorry, Mr. Leland. -Never mind.

761
00:51:10,419 --> 00:51:14,047
- 李蘭先生，你對玫瑰花蕾知道些什麼？ -“玫瑰花蕾”？
-What do you know about Rosebud? -"Rosebud"?

762
00:51:15,048 --> 00:51:18,260
他的臨終遺言?“玫瑰花蕾”
His dying words: "Rosebud."

763
00:51:18,593 --> 00:51:20,721
我在《問事報》上看到的
I saw that in the Inquirer.

764
00:51:21,722 --> 00:51:24,725
不過我從來不相信《問事報》上的任何東西
I never believed anything I saw in the Inquirer.

765
00:51:24,766 --> 00:51:26,226
還有別的事嗎？
Anything else?

766
00:51:26,268 --> 00:51:29,980
我可以和你談談愛米麗 我曾經和她一起上過舞蹈學校
I can tell you about Emily. I went to dancing school with Emily.

767
00:51:30,397 --> 00:51:32,149
我是文質彬彬的
I was very graceful.

768
00:51:33,108 --> 00:51:36,486
- 我們在談第一位凱恩夫人 - 她怎麼樣？
-We were talking about the first Mrs. Kane. -What was she like?

769
00:51:36,570 --> 00:51:39,072
和我在舞蹈學校婸{識的其他姑娘一樣
She was like all the girls I knew in dancing school.

770
00:51:39,156 --> 00:51:42,200
全都是好姑娘，愛米麗更好一點
Very nice girl. Emily was a little nicer.

771
00:51:43,660 --> 00:51:45,746
在結婚兩個月以後…
After the first couple of months...

772
00:51:45,787 --> 00:51:50,125
…她和查利除了吃早餐以外，很少見面
...she and Charlie didn't see much of each other except at breakfast.

773
00:51:50,792 --> 00:51:53,420
他們的婚姻和其他人的一樣
It was a marriage just like any other marriage.

774
00:52:03,639 --> 00:52:05,349
- 你真美 - 過獎了
-You're beautiful. -l can't be.

775
00:52:05,432 --> 00:52:07,184
你的確很漂亮
Yes, you are. You're very beautiful.

776
00:52:07,267 --> 00:52:09,811
我過去從來沒有一個晚上參加過六個宴會
I've never been to six parties in one night before.

777
00:52:10,062 --> 00:52:12,814
- 我也從來沒有這樣晚才起床 - 這只是個習慣問題
-I've never been up this late. -It抯 a matter of habit.

778
00:52:12,898 --> 00:52:15,859
- 僕人們會怎麼看？ - 認為我們過得愉快啊，對嗎？
-What will the servants think? -That we enjoyed ourselves.

779
00:52:15,942 --> 00:52:18,445
你為什麼要馬上去報館？
Why do you have to go straight off to the newspaper?

780
00:52:18,528 --> 00:52:22,240
你真不該嫁給一個辦報的人 他們比水手還糟
You never should've married a newspaperman, they're worse than sailors.

781
00:52:23,158 --> 00:52:25,077
我絕對地愛你
I absolutely adore you.

782
00:52:25,911 --> 00:52:28,830
查理斯，就是辦報人也得睡覺嘛
Charles, even newspapermen have to sleep.

783
00:52:30,332 --> 00:52:33,752
那我給伯恩斯坦打個電話 讓他把我的約會推遲到中午
I'll call Mr. Bernstein and have him put off my appointments till noon.

784
00:52:35,087 --> 00:52:36,171
現在幾點鐘啦？
What time is it?

785
00:52:36,838 --> 00:52:38,465
不知道，很晚了
I don't know. It's late.

786
00:52:40,842 --> 00:52:42,803
是很早了
It's early.

787
00:52:42,886 --> 00:52:44,596
查理斯…
Charles....

788
00:52:45,180 --> 00:52:48,183
你知道昨晚你讓我等了多久嗎？
Do you know how long you kept me waiting last night...

789
00:52:48,225 --> 00:52:51,061
你說要去報社十分鐘？
...when you went to the newspaper for 10 minutes?

790
00:52:51,311 --> 00:52:54,481
你深更半夜在報社媟F什麼？
What do you do in a newspaper in the middle of the night?

791
00:52:54,648 --> 00:52:59,653
親愛的，你唯一的通訊員就是《問事報》
My dear, your only correspondent is the Inquirer.

792
00:52:59,695 --> 00:53:02,531
有時候我更喜歡血肉之爭
Sometimes I think I'd prefer a rival of flesh and blood.

793
00:53:02,572 --> 00:53:05,158
在報紙上我可沒花那麼多時間
I don't spend that much time on the newspaper.

794
00:53:05,200 --> 00:53:09,329
不是時間的問題 而是你印刷出來的東西，是在攻擊總統
It isn't just the time. It's what you print, attacking the President.

795
00:53:09,371 --> 00:53:12,624
- 你是指約翰叔叔 - 我是指美國總統
-You mean Uncle John. -l mean the President of the United States.

796
00:53:12,708 --> 00:53:15,168
他還是約翰叔叔，一個好心腸的傻子…
He's still Uncle John and a well-meaning fathead...

797
00:53:15,210 --> 00:53:18,630
他讓一夥兒不要命的騙子來管理他的政府
...who's letting a pack of high-pressure crooks run his administration.

798
00:53:18,714 --> 00:53:22,509
- 整個石油醜聞… - 恰巧是他當總統，查理斯，而不是你
-This whole oil scandal-- -He happens to be the President, not you.

799
00:53:22,551 --> 00:53:25,387
這個錯誤早晚要糾正過來
That's a mistake that will be corrected one of these days.

800
00:53:25,470 --> 00:53:30,726
你的那位伯恩斯坦先生昨天給小凱恩 帶來了極度的不愉快
Your Mr. Bernstein sent Junior the most incredible atrocity yesterday.

801
00:53:31,727 --> 00:53:34,396
我絕對不能允許這種情況出現在保育園
I simply can't have it in the nursery.

802
00:53:36,523 --> 00:53:39,818
伯恩斯坦先生只是偶爾去保育園看看
Mr. Bernstein is apt to pay a visit to the nursery now and then.

803
00:53:39,901 --> 00:53:41,486
非去不可嗎？
Does he have to?

804
00:53:42,529 --> 00:53:43,572
是的
Yes.

805
00:53:43,697 --> 00:53:48,118
- 真的，查理別人會想… - 那得要看我讓他們怎麼想
-Really, Charles, people will think-- -What I tell them to think.

806
00:54:06,928 --> 00:54:08,972
難道他不曾愛過她嗎？
Wasn't he ever in love with her?

807
00:54:09,139 --> 00:54:10,891
他是為愛情而結婚的
He married for love.

808
00:54:11,808 --> 00:54:13,185
愛情
Love.

809
00:54:13,852 --> 00:54:15,562
所以他什麼事都做了
That is why he did everything.

810
00:54:15,646 --> 00:54:18,607
所以他又去搞政治了 仿佛有了我們這些人還不夠
That's why he went into politics. It seems we weren't enough.

811
00:54:18,690 --> 00:54:21,735
他還要所有的選民也都愛他
He wanted all the voters to love him, too.

812
00:54:22,444 --> 00:54:24,946
他真正從生活中所要求的就是愛
All he wanted out of life was love.

813
00:54:25,781 --> 00:54:28,992
查利的故事就是：他怎樣失去了愛
That's Charlie's story. How he lost it.

814
00:54:29,201 --> 00:54:32,412
你知道嗎？他就是不願意付出（愛）
You see, he just didn't have any to give.

815
00:54:33,413 --> 00:54:36,208
當然，他愛查利·凱恩
He loved Charlie Kane, of course.

816
00:54:36,792 --> 00:54:38,210
非常愛
Very dearly.

817
00:54:38,961 --> 00:54:41,171
還有他的母親，我猜他始終愛她的
And his mother, I guess he always loved her.

818
00:54:41,254 --> 00:54:44,299
- 那麼他的第二位妻子呢？ - 蘇珊·亞歷山大嗎？
-How about his second wife? -Susan Alexander?

819
00:54:45,092 --> 00:54:47,260
你知道查利把她稱作什麼？
You know what Charlie called her?

820
00:54:47,469 --> 00:54:50,222
他遇見她後的第二天，跟我談到她
The day after he'd met her, he told me about her.

821
00:54:50,389 --> 00:54:55,310
他說她是“美國公眾的橫截面” （指很一般的人）
He said she was "a cross-section of the American public."

822
00:54:57,521 --> 00:55:01,149
我猜他是不由自主了 她準有什麼東西吸引住了他
I guess he couldn't help it. She must have had something for him.

823
00:55:01,316 --> 00:55:04,069
第一次見面的晚上，據查利說…
That first night, according to Charlie...

824
00:55:05,153 --> 00:55:07,489
她就是牙痛
...all she had was a toothache.

825
00:55:38,520 --> 00:55:41,064
有什麼可笑的？
What are you laughing at, young lady?

826
00:55:42,941 --> 00:55:45,694
- 你怎麼回事？ - 牙痛
-What's the matter with you? -Toothache.

827
00:55:45,777 --> 00:55:47,529
- 什麼？ - 牙痛
-What? -Toothache.

828
00:55:47,612 --> 00:55:48,947
牙痛？
Toothache?

829
00:55:52,367 --> 00:55:54,411
你是說你牙痛
You mean you've got a toothache.

830
00:55:55,329 --> 00:55:58,206
- 有什麼可笑的？ - 你很好笑，先生
-What's funny about that? -You're funny, mister.

831
00:55:58,290 --> 00:56:00,876
- 你臉上有髒東西 - 不是髒東西，是泥巴
-You've got dirt on your face. -Not dirt, it's mud.

832
00:56:00,959 --> 00:56:03,253
你想要點熱水嗎？我就住在這
Do you want some hot water? I live right here.

833
00:56:03,337 --> 00:56:05,297
什麼意思，小姐？
What's that, young lady?

834
00:56:06,548 --> 00:56:09,009
我是說，如果你想進來洗洗臉…
I said, if you wanted some hot water...

835
00:56:09,301 --> 00:56:13,472
…我可以給你弄點兒熱水
...l could get you some...hot water.

836
00:56:17,059 --> 00:56:19,394
好的，非常感謝
All right, thank you very much.

837
00:56:33,742 --> 00:56:35,702
現在我看起來好點了嗎？
Do I look any better now?

838
00:56:35,744 --> 00:56:40,499
- 這種藥一點效果都沒有 - 現在你要做的就是不要去想它
-This medicine doesn't do a bit of good. -What you need is to get your mind off it.

839
00:56:45,671 --> 00:56:48,799
對不起，我的女房東希望我把房門敞開…
Excuse me, but my landlady prefers me to keep this door open...

840
00:56:49,049 --> 00:56:52,052
-…如果有先生來訪的話 - 好的
-...when I have a gentleman caller. -All right.

841
00:56:52,094 --> 00:56:54,221
牙又痛了嗎？
You have got a toothache, haven't you?

842
00:56:54,262 --> 00:56:57,349
- 是的 - 倒不如繼續笑我啊
-l surely have. -Why don't you try laughing at me again?

843
00:56:57,432 --> 00:56:59,393
- 什麼？ - 我和剛才在街上一樣可笑
-What? -I? still pretty funny.

844
00:56:59,434 --> 00:57:02,062
我知道，不過你不喜歡我笑你
I know, but you don't want me to laugh at you.

845
00:57:02,104 --> 00:57:04,189
可我也不願讓你牙痛
I don't want your tooth to hurt, either.

846
00:57:04,272 --> 00:57:05,565
看著我
Look at me.

847
00:57:05,983 --> 00:57:07,109
看到了嗎？
See that?

848
00:57:07,192 --> 00:57:08,527
你在幹什麼？
What are you doing?

849
00:57:08,610 --> 00:57:11,071
我兩隻耳朵在動
I'm wiggling both my ears at the same time.

850
00:57:13,281 --> 00:57:15,075
就這樣，好笑吧
That's it, smile.

851
00:57:17,744 --> 00:57:21,581
我在全世界最好的男校 念了整整兩年書才學會這個把戲
It took me two solid years at the best boys' school in the world to learn that.

852
00:57:21,623 --> 00:57:24,835
那個教會我的人現在是委內瑞拉的總統
The fellow who taught me is now president of Venezuela.

853
00:57:26,795 --> 00:57:28,213
這就好了
That's it!

854
00:57:32,009 --> 00:57:34,594
- 是長頸鹿？ - 不，不是的
-Is it a giraffe? -No, not a giraffe.

855
00:57:34,678 --> 00:57:37,597
- 我敢說一定是 - 什麼？
-l bet it is. -What?

856
00:57:37,639 --> 00:57:39,766
那就是大象
Well, then it's an elephant.

857
00:57:39,975 --> 00:57:43,687
- 是隻公雞 - 公雞！
-It抯 supposed to be a rooster. -A rooster!

858
00:57:44,187 --> 00:57:48,025
你的把戲真不少 你是職業魔術師嗎？
You know an awful lot of tricks. Are you a professional magician?

859
00:57:48,108 --> 00:57:50,694
- 不，我不是魔術師 - 我開玩笑的
-No, I'm not a magician. -l was just joking.

860
00:57:50,777 --> 00:57:52,446
你真的不知道我是誰？
You really don't know who I am?

861
00:57:52,487 --> 00:57:55,616
你說過你的名字，凱恩先生 但我相當的無知
You told me your name, Mr. Kane, but I'm awfully ignorant.

862
00:57:55,657 --> 00:58:00,162
我猜你能理解 我打賭你的名字我聽了不下一百萬次
I guess you caught on to that. I bet I've heard your name a million times.

863
00:58:00,329 --> 00:58:03,457
可是你很喜歡我，是嗎？ 儘管你不知道我是誰
You really like me, though, even though you don't know who I am?

864
00:58:03,498 --> 00:58:06,960
是的，你太有意思了！
I surely do. You've been wonderful.

865
00:58:08,045 --> 00:58:10,797
要不是你，我真的不知道該怎麼辦
Without you I don't know what I would have done.

866
00:58:10,839 --> 00:58:14,176
我牙齒痛，認識的人也不多
I had a toothache, and I don't know many people.

867
00:58:14,509 --> 00:58:16,386
可我認識的人太多了
I know too many people.

868
00:58:16,845 --> 00:58:18,847
我猜我們兩人都很孤獨
I guess we're both lonely.

869
00:58:19,181 --> 00:58:23,143
想知道我在禮服弄贓之前準備幹什麼嗎？
Want to know what I was going to do before I ruined my best Sunday clothes?

870
00:58:23,185 --> 00:58:26,480
我敢打賭那不是你的禮服 你大概有不少衣服
I bet they're not your best Sunday clothes. You probably have more.

871
00:58:26,521 --> 00:58:27,731
我只是跟你開開玩笑！
I was just joking.

872
00:58:29,483 --> 00:58:33,403
我正要去西曼哈頓的倉庫…
I was on my way to the Western Manhattan Warehouse...

873
00:58:33,487 --> 00:58:35,489
去尋找我的童年
...in search of my youth.

874
00:58:36,573 --> 00:58:41,203
你知道嗎，我母親去世已經很久了 她的遺物全都放在西部
You see, my mother died a long time ago. Her things were put in storage out West.

875
00:58:41,286 --> 00:58:43,747
因為那時沒有地方擱這些東西
There wasn't any other place to put them.

876
00:58:43,830 --> 00:58:47,876
我本想現在派人去取回來 我今晚本想去看看的
I thought I'd send for them now. Tonight I was going to take a look at them.

877
00:58:47,960 --> 00:58:50,170
這是個傷感的旅行
A sort of sentimental journey.

878
00:58:53,757 --> 00:58:56,093
我辦了幾家報紙，你呢？
I run a couple of newspapers. What do you do?

879
00:58:56,176 --> 00:58:57,177
我？
Me?

880
00:58:57,469 --> 00:58:59,680
- 你說你多大了？ - 我沒說過
-How old did you say you were? -l didn't say.

881
00:58:59,763 --> 00:59:02,474
如果你說過，我就不會問你第二遍了
If you had, I wouldn't have asked you.

882
00:59:02,557 --> 00:59:03,809
- 多大啦？ - 不小了
-How old? -Pretty old.

883
00:59:03,892 --> 00:59:05,978
- 多大？ - 到八月就二十二了
-How old? -Twenty-two in August.

884
00:59:06,061 --> 00:59:08,063
成熟的年齡，你幹什麼工作？
That's a ripe old age. What do you do?

885
00:59:08,146 --> 00:59:11,608
我在賽利格曼公司工作 負責背景音樂
I work at Seligman's. I'm in charge of the sheet music.

886
00:59:11,900 --> 00:59:16,488
- 這就是你想幹的工作嗎？ - 不，我曾想當個歌手
-Is that what you want to do? -No, I wanted to be a singer, I guess.

887
00:59:17,239 --> 00:59:20,826
- 我是說，我母親想讓我當 - 後來怎麼沒唱呢？
-That is, I didn't. My mother did for me. -What happened to the singing?

888
00:59:20,909 --> 00:59:24,913
母親總是認為，她經常談到要我唱歌劇
Mother always thought, she always talked about grand opera for me.

889
00:59:24,997 --> 00:59:26,206
你想想
Imagine.

890
00:59:26,498 --> 00:59:30,711
可是，我的嗓子不是那種類型的 只是…，你知道做媽媽的總是那樣的
But my voice isn't that kind. It's just, you know what mothers are like.

891
00:59:32,504 --> 00:59:33,714
是的
Yes.

892
00:59:35,757 --> 00:59:38,552
- 這埵鹵琴嗎？ - 鋼琴？
-Have you got a piano? -A piano?

893
00:59:39,553 --> 00:59:41,346
有，在客廳
Yes, there's one in the parlor.

894
00:59:41,430 --> 00:59:44,474
- 你能唱給我聽嗎？ - 你是不會喜歡聽我唱的
-Would you sing for me? -You wouldn't want to hear me sing.

895
00:59:44,558 --> 00:59:45,934
我會喜歡的
Yes, I would.

896
00:59:47,728 --> 00:59:49,980
別把牙痛當藉口來推脫
Don't tell me your toothache is bothering you.

897
00:59:50,063 --> 00:59:51,773
不痛，全好了
No, that's all gone.

898
00:59:53,525 --> 00:59:55,485
那好
All right.

899
00:59:56,445 --> 00:59:58,238
我們去客廳吧
Let's go to the parlor.

900
00:59:58,280 --> 01:00:04,119
Yes，Lindor shall be mine
"Yes, Lindor shall be mine

901
01:00:05,495 --> 01:00:09,041
I have sworn it
"l have sworn it

902
01:00:09,916 --> 01:00:12,753
For weal or woe
"For weal or woe

903
01:00:14,838 --> 01:00:17,591
Yes，Lindor
"Yes, Lindor

904
01:00:24,348 --> 01:00:27,643
Lo giurai
"Lo giurai

905
01:00:29,061 --> 01:00:32,981
La vincer？
"La vincer?

906
01:00:40,989 --> 01:00:43,492
只有一個人可以擺脫本州…
There is only one man who can rid the politics...

907
01:00:43,533 --> 01:00:46,828
…吉姆格蒂斯的邪惡政治統治
...of this state of the evil domination of Boss Jim Gettys.

908
01:00:46,912 --> 01:00:50,832
我是查理斯·福斯特·凱恩先生的發言人 他為自由而戰…
I am speaking of Charles Foster Kane, the fighting liberal...

909
01:00:50,874 --> 01:00:54,461
是勞動者的朋友，必將成為下一任州長…
...the friend of the workingman, the next governor of this state...

910
01:00:54,503 --> 01:00:56,797
參加這次競選…
...who entered upon this campaign....

911
01:00:56,838 --> 01:00:58,840
只有一個目的?
...with one purpose only:

912
01:00:58,882 --> 01:01:03,261
就是廣泛揭露…
To point out and make public the dishonesty...

913
01:01:03,512 --> 01:01:08,308
吉姆·W·格蒂斯政治機器十足的惡行和欺詐
...the downright villainy of Boss Jim W. Gettys' political machine...

914
01:01:08,600 --> 01:01:12,938
當前他們完全控制了本州的政權
...now in complete control of the government of this state.

915
01:01:13,355 --> 01:01:17,150
我沒有競選宣言
I made no campaign promises...

916
01:01:17,651 --> 01:01:22,281
因為直到幾周以前，我都沒有當選的希望
...because, until a few weeks ago, I had no hope of being elected.

917
01:01:23,907 --> 01:01:28,078
不過現在我不只是指望而已
Now, however, l have something more than a hope.

918
01:01:31,331 --> 01:01:33,834
吉姆·格蒂斯沒機會了
Jim Gettys has something less than a chance.

919
01:01:38,255 --> 01:01:40,173
每一個投票測驗
Every straw vote...

920
01:01:40,340 --> 01:01:45,178
每一個獨立的民意測驗都表明我將會當選
...every independent poll shows that l will be elected.

921
01:01:45,595 --> 01:01:47,306
那麼
Very well.

922
01:01:47,472 --> 01:01:50,225
現在我可以作出一些許諾了
Now l can afford to make some promises.

923
01:02:00,527 --> 01:02:02,696
勞動者和平民區的孩子們知道…
The workingman and the slum child...

924
01:02:02,738 --> 01:02:07,909
他們能指望我為他們的利益竭盡所能
...know they can expect my best efforts in their interests.

925
01:02:07,993 --> 01:02:12,539
正派的公民們知道，我將盡力去…
The decent, ordinary citizens know that I?l do everything in my power...

926
01:02:12,623 --> 01:02:17,836
保護非特權階層、低收入階層和貧困階層
...to protect the underprivileged, the underpaid, and the underfed.

927
01:02:21,757 --> 01:02:26,136
- 媽媽，爸爸是州長嗎？ - 還不是，小寶貝
-Mother, is Pop governor yet? -Not yet, Junior.

928
01:02:30,015 --> 01:02:33,393
我現在承諾
I'd make my promises now...

929
01:02:33,685 --> 01:02:37,147
只要不是太忙我都能兌現（笑）
...if I weren't too busy arranging to keep them.

930
01:02:41,735 --> 01:02:44,738
但是我所許下的其中一個諾言
But here's one promise I?l make...

931
01:02:44,821 --> 01:02:47,866
吉姆·格蒂斯知道我會兌現的
...and Boss Jim Gettys knows I?l keep it.

932
01:02:49,159 --> 01:02:51,995
作為州長我首先要做的
My first official act as governor of this state...

933
01:02:52,412 --> 01:02:57,292
就是委任一名專門的地方檢查官
...will be to appoint a special district attorney to arrange for the indictment...

934
01:02:57,501 --> 01:03:03,215
對吉姆·格蒂斯提出起訴，控告並定罪
...prosecution and conviction of Boss Jim W. Gettys.

935
01:03:29,449 --> 01:03:32,661
如果今天舉行投票，你一定會以十萬票當選
If the election were held today, you'd be in by 100,000 votes.

936
01:03:32,703 --> 01:03:34,579
- 格蒂斯甚至裝不下去了 - 爸爸
-Gettys isn't even pretending. -Pop.

937
01:03:34,663 --> 01:03:36,790
- 哈羅，小夥計！ - 他不僅是嚇壞了，他病倒了
-Hello, son. -He isn't just scared, he's sick.

938
01:03:36,873 --> 01:03:39,710
我看吉姆·格蒂斯總該悟出，我是說到做到的
It's beginning to dawn on Jim Gettys I mean what I say.

939
01:03:39,793 --> 01:03:43,171
- 你喜歡你老子的演講嗎？ - 我每個字都聽得清楚
-Did you like your old man's speech? -l could hear every word.

940
01:03:43,213 --> 01:03:44,881
- 哈羅，愛米麗 - 注意！
-Hello, Emily. -Hold it.

941
01:03:45,465 --> 01:03:48,135
- 妙極了，凱恩先生！ - 妙極了
-Great speech, Mr. Kane. -Wonderful.

942
01:03:48,176 --> 01:03:50,512
你要找一輛計程車嗎？
Will you get us a taxi?

943
01:03:51,888 --> 01:03:54,808
我讓奧利弗開車送小凱恩回家
I'm sending Junior home in the car with Oliver.

944
01:03:55,183 --> 01:03:56,810
晚安，爸爸
Good night, Father.

945
01:03:58,145 --> 01:04:00,022
再見，兒子
Goodbye, son.

946
01:04:10,699 --> 01:04:14,161
為什麼用車送小凱恩回家？ 你做計程車幹什麼？
Why did you send Junior home in the car? What are you doing in a taxi?

947
01:04:14,244 --> 01:04:16,413
我要你和我一起去拜訪一家人，查理斯
There's a call I want you to make with me.

948
01:04:16,496 --> 01:04:18,415
- 著什麼急 - 不，不能等
-It can wait. -No, it can't.

949
01:04:18,498 --> 01:04:20,167
這是怎麼回事，愛米麗？
What's this all about, Emily?

950
01:04:20,250 --> 01:04:23,503
可能什麼事情也沒有，我只想弄清楚
It may not be about anything at all. I intend to find out.

951
01:04:23,587 --> 01:04:27,674
- 你要去哪裡？ - 我要去“西74街，185號”
-Where are you going? -I? going to "185 West 74th Street."

952
01:04:29,217 --> 01:04:32,137
如果你願意的話，你可以和我一起去
If you wish, you may come with me.

953
01:04:36,308 --> 01:04:37,851
我和你一起去
I'll come with you.

954
01:04:43,023 --> 01:04:46,485
我不知道你還有這種瞎胡鬧的本事，愛米麗
I had no idea you had this flair for melodrama, Emily.

955
01:04:48,070 --> 01:04:50,072
進來，凱恩先生
Come right in, Mr. Kane.

956
01:05:00,624 --> 01:05:02,000
查利
Charlie.

957
01:05:08,715 --> 01:05:11,802
他逼著我給你妻子送去那張紙條 我本不想那樣做
He forced me to send your wife that letter. I didn't want to.

958
01:05:11,885 --> 01:05:14,680
他說得非常可怕…
He's been saying the most terrible....

959
01:05:18,976 --> 01:05:20,644
凱恩夫人
Mrs. Kane.

960
01:05:22,646 --> 01:05:25,148
我看不會有人來給我們介紹的
I don't suppose anybody would introduce us.

961
01:05:26,608 --> 01:05:28,193
我是吉姆·格蒂斯
I'm Jim Gettys.

962
01:05:28,777 --> 01:05:29,945
什麼事？
Yes?

963
01:05:33,198 --> 01:05:36,952
是我讓亞歷山大小姐給你這個條子的
I made Miss Alexander send you the note, Mrs. Kane.

964
01:05:36,994 --> 01:05:39,288
她開始有點兒不太願意，不過她還是做了
She didn't want to at first. But she did it.

965
01:05:39,329 --> 01:05:42,165
查利，他對我說的事…，他威脅要…
Charlie, the things he said to me.... He threatened to--

966
01:05:43,292 --> 01:05:47,129
我看我用不著等到當選後再對你採取行動 頭一件事，我看我該扭斷你的脖子
I won't wait until I'm elected. To start with, I think I'll break your neck.

967
01:05:47,212 --> 01:05:49,965
也許你能辦得到，也許你辦不到
Maybe you can do it, and maybe you can't.

968
01:05:51,049 --> 01:05:55,178
查理斯！你想要扭斷這個人的脖子 絲毫不能解釋這封信?
Your breaking this man's neck would scarcely explain this note:

969
01:05:56,138 --> 01:05:59,975
“對凱恩先生，對你自己，對你的兒子 將會有嚴重後果”
"Serious consequences for Mr. Kane, for yourself and for your son."

970
01:06:00,058 --> 01:06:03,103
- 他想讓他來這堙K - 這封信是什麼意思？
-He wanted to get her to come here-- -What does this note mean?

971
01:06:03,145 --> 01:06:05,772
我是蘇珊·亞歷山大 我知道你會怎麼想…
I'm Susan Alexander. I know what you're thinking--

972
01:06:05,814 --> 01:06:08,650
- 這封信是什麼意思，亞歷山大小姐？ - 她不知道，凱恩夫人
-What does this note mean, Ms. Alexander? -She don't know.

973
01:06:08,734 --> 01:06:11,570
她只是發出這封信，因為我告訴她 不發出這封信，對她沒有什麼好處
She sent it because I told her it wouldn't be smart not to.

974
01:06:11,653 --> 01:06:14,948
- 愛米麗，這位紳士… - 我不是紳士
-Emily, this gentleman-- -I? not a gentleman.

975
01:06:15,157 --> 01:06:18,035
你丈夫是想取笑我，才叫我紳士
Your husband is only trying to be funny calling me one.

976
01:06:18,118 --> 01:06:20,704
我甚至不知道紳士是什麼
I don't even know what a gentleman is.

977
01:06:21,747 --> 01:06:25,000
你明白嗎？我認為一個紳士…
You see, my idea of a gentleman....

978
01:06:28,170 --> 01:06:31,632
凱恩夫人，如果我有一家報紙 而我不同意某人或某位政客的…
If I owned a paper and didn't like the way somebody was doing things...

979
01:06:31,673 --> 01:06:34,134
做事方法，我就用我所掌握的一切 來和他鬥爭
...some politician, I'd fight him with all I had.

980
01:06:34,176 --> 01:06:36,011
但是我不會把對方醜化成一個 穿著條紋號衣的囚犯
I wouldn't show him in a convict suit...

981
01:06:36,094 --> 01:06:38,472
使他的家人可以在報紙上看到那樣的漫畫
...so his family could see his picture in the paper.

982
01:06:38,513 --> 01:06:42,476
- 你是一個卑鄙的貪官污吏… - 現在我們討論你是什麼東西
-You're a cheap, crooked grafter-- -We're talking now about what you are.

983
01:06:43,393 --> 01:06:46,229
凱恩夫人，我是在為我的生命而戰 不僅是我的政治前途，而是生命
I'm fighting for my life, not just my political life.

984
01:06:46,313 --> 01:06:48,482
- 他說除非你… - 我要說的是…
-He said unless you-- -That's what I said.

985
01:06:48,565 --> 01:06:52,569
這是我願意給你的一次機會 比你給我的機會要多
Here's the chance I'm willing to give him. It's more of a chance than he'd give me.

986
01:06:52,653 --> 01:06:57,407
除非他今天晚上承認他病情嚴重 必須修養一二年…
Unless he decides by tomorrow that he's so sick he has to go away for a year...

987
01:06:57,491 --> 01:07:01,787
那麼星期一早上，本州除了你們以外的 所有報紙都將刊登我提供給他們的新聞
...Monday morning, all papers in the state, except his, will carry the story I'll give.

988
01:07:01,870 --> 01:07:03,246
什麼新聞？
What story?

989
01:07:04,039 --> 01:07:07,209
- 關於他和亞歷山大小姐的新聞 - 我們沒有任何新聞！
-The story about him and Ms. Alexander. -There isn't any story!

990
01:07:07,292 --> 01:07:08,502
閉嘴！
Shut up.

991
01:07:08,877 --> 01:07:11,713
- 我們得到的證據可能比頭條新聞更壞 - 凱恩先生只是…
We've got evidence that would look bad in the headlines.

992
01:07:11,755 --> 01:07:14,424
你想要我把證據拿出來嗎？
Do you want me to give you the evidence?

993
01:07:16,551 --> 01:07:19,388
我希望凱恩先生而退出競選 那條新聞就無需發表了
I'd rather he withdrew without having the story published.

994
01:07:19,429 --> 01:07:22,516
不是我關心他，那樣對我好一些
Not that I care about him, but I'd be better off that way.

995
01:07:25,435 --> 01:07:27,521
對你也一樣，凱恩夫人
So would you, Mrs. Kane.

996
01:07:27,938 --> 01:07:30,023
那我怎麼辦？
What about me?

997
01:07:32,025 --> 01:07:35,862
他說我將名譽掃地，不論我到哪裡…
He said my name would be dragged through the mud. That everywhere I went--

998
01:07:35,904 --> 01:07:38,782
我看這是你唯一的選擇，查理斯
There seems to be only one decision you can make, Charles.

999
01:07:39,408 --> 01:07:41,576
我看你只有此路一條
I'd say that it'd been made for you.

1000
01:07:43,245 --> 01:07:45,330
你說說，本州的選民將…
You can't tell me the voters of this state--

1001
01:07:45,580 --> 01:07:48,375
目前我對本州的選民不感興趣
I'm not interested in the voters of this state right now.

1002
01:07:48,417 --> 01:07:49,918
我感興趣的是我的兒子
I am interested in our son.

1003
01:07:49,960 --> 01:07:53,130
- 查利！如果他們發表了這個故事… - 他們不會的
-Charlie, if they publish this story-- -They won't.

1004
01:07:54,423 --> 01:07:56,550
晚安，格蒂斯先生
Good night, Mr. Gettys.

1005
01:08:05,475 --> 01:08:07,561
你跟我來嗎，查理斯？
Are you coming, Charles?

1006
01:08:09,813 --> 01:08:11,148
不
No.

1007
01:08:14,568 --> 01:08:16,194
我要留在這
I'm staying here.

1008
01:08:19,323 --> 01:08:21,408
我可以單獨處理這事
I can fight this all alone.

1009
01:08:22,659 --> 01:08:25,162
如果你失去理智，可能會追悔莫及
If you don't listen to reason, it may be too late.

1010
01:08:25,245 --> 01:08:29,207
莫及？對什麼而言？
Too late? For what?

1011
01:08:31,293 --> 01:08:34,588
是對你和這個公賊…
For you and this public thief...

1012
01:08:34,921 --> 01:08:37,257
想奪走選民對我的愛而言的吧？
...to take the love of the people away from me?

1013
01:08:37,299 --> 01:08:40,093
你還要考慮一下其他事情，你的兒子
You got other things to think about. Your little boy.

1014
01:08:40,218 --> 01:08:42,679
你不是不願意他在報紙上讀到你的新聞
You don't want him to read about you in the papers.

1015
01:08:42,763 --> 01:08:47,267
在這世界上只有一個人能決定我該做什麼 那就是我自己
There's only one person in the world to decide what I'll do. And that's me.

1016
01:08:50,145 --> 01:08:53,690
你是決定過你該做什麼，查理斯，那是以前
You decided what you were going to do, Charles, some time ago.

1017
01:09:00,948 --> 01:09:03,617
你比我設想的還要愚蠢，凱恩先生
You're making a bigger fool of yourself than I thought.

1018
01:09:03,659 --> 01:09:06,036
- 我跟你沒話可說 - 你輸了…
-I抳e got nothing to say to you. -You're licked--

1019
01:09:06,119 --> 01:09:09,498
滾出去！如果想要見我，叫典獄長給我寫信
Get out. If you want to see me, have the warden write me a letter.

1020
01:09:09,748 --> 01:09:14,419
如果換個人，我會對他說： 將要發生的事對你是個教訓
If it was anybody else, I'd say what's going to happen to you would be a lesson to you.

1021
01:09:14,670 --> 01:09:17,381
不過你需要的不止是一次教訓
Only you're going to need more than one lesson.

1022
01:09:18,215 --> 01:09:22,260
- 而且你肯定要吃夠教訓的 - 用不著為我操心，格蒂斯
-And you'll get more than one lesson. -Don't worry about me, Gettys.

1023
01:09:23,929 --> 01:09:25,973
用不著為我操心！
Don't worry about me!

1024
01:09:26,890 --> 01:09:29,476
我是查理斯·福斯特·凱恩！
I'm Charles Foster Kane!

1025
01:09:30,060 --> 01:09:34,356
我不是骯髒卑鄙的政客 想要使自己…
I'm no cheap, crooked politician trying to save himself...

1026
01:09:34,398 --> 01:09:37,442
…逃脫法律的嚴懲！
...from the consequences of his crimes!

1027
01:09:38,485 --> 01:09:42,489
格蒂斯！我要把你送進新新監獄
Gettys! I'm gonna send you to Sing Sing.

1028
01:09:42,698 --> 01:09:44,825
新新監獄，格蒂斯
Sing Sing, Gettys.

1029
01:09:48,036 --> 01:09:51,123
- 要車嗎，凱恩夫人？ - 好的，謝謝你
-Have you a car, Mrs. Kane? -Yes, thank you.

1030
01:09:51,665 --> 01:09:54,418
- 晚安 - 晚安
-Good night. -Good night.

1031
01:10:05,220 --> 01:10:09,182
快來看，號外！號外！
Paper. Read all about it. Extra, extra.

1032
01:10:13,729 --> 01:10:15,814
- 買報嗎？ - 不，謝謝
-Paper? -No, thanks.

1033
01:10:30,704 --> 01:10:33,540
已經有一百萬張占多數的票反對…
With a million majority already against him...

1034
01:10:33,790 --> 01:10:37,127
[號外：凱恩當選] 只有教區的選票還沒有出來…
...and the church counties still to be heard from...

1035
01:10:37,336 --> 01:10:39,755
大概沒有指望了
...I? afraid we got no choice.

1036
01:10:39,838 --> 01:10:41,256
這一張？
This one?

1037
01:10:44,718 --> 01:10:46,470
那一張吧
That one.

1038
01:11:09,785 --> 01:11:11,620
晚安
Good night again.

1039
01:11:22,798 --> 01:11:26,259
- 我能做點什麼嗎？ - 沒有，伯恩斯坦先生
-Is there anything I can-- -No, thanks, Mr. Bernstein.

1040
01:11:27,928 --> 01:11:30,222
你最好回家睡覺
You better go home and get some sleep.

1041
01:11:31,306 --> 01:11:32,766
你也是
You, too.

1042
01:11:35,185 --> 01:11:36,979
晚安，凱恩先生
Good night, Mr. Kane.

1043
01:12:02,129 --> 01:12:04,673
- 哈羅，傑德 - 我喝多了
-Hello, Jedediah. -I? drunk.

1044
01:12:08,343 --> 01:12:13,473
如果你喝醉的目的就是要和我談…
If you've got drunk to talk to me about...

1045
01:12:16,018 --> 01:12:18,562
…蘇珊·亞歷山大，就別費心了
...Ms. Alexander, don't bother.

1046
01:12:20,397 --> 01:12:22,190
我不感興趣
I'm not interested.

1047
01:12:26,403 --> 01:12:30,282
我已經使神聖的改革事業倒退了，對嗎？
I've set back the sacred cause of reform, is that it?

1048
01:12:31,742 --> 01:12:33,160
不錯
All right.

1049
01:12:34,911 --> 01:12:38,206
如果他們自己希望如此 他們已經做出了選擇
If that's the way they want it, the people have made their choice.

1050
01:12:38,290 --> 01:12:41,084
顯然，本州的選民喜歡吉姆·格蒂斯 而不是喜歡我
It's obvious the people prefer Jim Gettys to me.

1051
01:12:41,168 --> 01:12:44,838
你談到選民，仿佛你擁有他們
You talk about the people as though you owned them.

1052
01:12:44,921 --> 01:12:47,215
仿佛他們是屬於你的，天啦
As though they belong to you. Goodness.

1053
01:12:47,966 --> 01:12:52,763
就我記憶所及，你談過“給予人民權力”…
As long as I can remember, you've talked about giving the people their rights...

1054
01:12:52,929 --> 01:12:56,183
就好像你能把自由作為禮物送給他們…
...as if you could make them a present of liberty...

1055
01:12:56,308 --> 01:12:58,852
作為他們為你服務的報酬
...as a reward for services rendered.

1056
01:12:58,894 --> 01:13:01,313
- 傑德 - 你記得那些勞動者嗎？
-Jed. -You remember the workingman?

1057
01:13:02,064 --> 01:13:04,691
我也要喝醉，傑德
I'll get drunk, too, Jedediah...

1058
01:13:06,193 --> 01:13:07,444
…如果這樣有用的話
...if it'll do any good.

1059
01:13:07,527 --> 01:13:10,948
沒有任何用處，你也從來都沒醉過
It won't do any good. Besides you never get drunk.

1060
01:13:11,073 --> 01:13:13,909
你經常奢談勞動者…
You used to write an awful lot about the workingman--

1061
01:13:13,951 --> 01:13:14,868
回去吧
Go on home.

1062
01:13:14,910 --> 01:13:17,788
可是，他們正在變成所謂的 “有組織的勞工”
He's turning into something called "organized labor."

1063
01:13:19,581 --> 01:13:22,918
你一點也不會喜歡的，當你發現…
You won't like that one little bit when you find out...

1064
01:13:23,001 --> 01:13:28,131
那意味著他們認為某種東西是他們的權利 而不是你的恩賜的時候！
...it means your workingman expects something as his right, and not your gift.

1065
01:13:30,217 --> 01:13:34,721
當你所珍視的無特權的人真正聯合起來…
When your precious underprivileged really get together....

1066
01:13:35,305 --> 01:13:37,140
噢，天啦
Oh, boy....

1067
01:13:37,933 --> 01:13:40,894
他們加在一起要比你那特權還要大…
That'll add up to something bigger than your privilege...

1068
01:13:40,978 --> 01:13:43,939
那時我就不知你會怎麼辦了
...then I don't know what you'll do.

1069
01:13:43,981 --> 01:13:49,278
也許，你會坐船到一個荒島去當猴王
Sail away to a desert island probably and lord it over the monkeys.

1070
01:13:50,570 --> 01:13:52,739
我用不著太操心了
I wouldn't worry about it too much.

1071
01:13:53,115 --> 01:13:57,995
在那堣]不愁沒有糾正我錯誤的人
There'll probably be a few of them there to tell me when I do something wrong.

1072
01:13:58,203 --> 01:14:00,289
你不能總是狗運亨通
You may not always be so lucky.

1073
01:14:01,123 --> 01:14:02,582
你還沒有喝醉
You're not very drunk.

1074
01:14:02,624 --> 01:14:04,668
喝醉？你關心什麼？
Drunk, what do you care?

1075
01:14:05,085 --> 01:14:07,963
除了你自己，你什麼也不關心
You don't care about anything except you.

1076
01:14:08,964 --> 01:14:14,803
你只是想使人們相信你非常熱愛他們 因此他們應當回報你的愛
You persuade people that you love them so much that they ought to love you back.

1077
01:14:15,137 --> 01:14:17,764
你需要的是你自己方式的愛
Only you want love on your own terms.

1078
01:14:19,474 --> 01:14:22,936
那是以你為準，根據你的規則來比賽
It's something to be played your way, according to your rules.

1079
01:14:29,568 --> 01:14:32,779
- 查利，希望你能讓我到芝加哥分社工作 - 什麼？
-Let me work on the Chicago paper. -What?

1080
01:14:33,071 --> 01:14:37,868
- 你不是說過，那婸搨n一個“戲劇…員” -“戲劇評論員”
You said you were looking for someone to do dramatic "crimitism," criticism.

1081
01:14:38,118 --> 01:14:39,828
我喝醉了
I am drunk.

1082
01:14:42,372 --> 01:14:44,374
我想去芝加哥
I want to go to Chicago.

1083
01:14:45,667 --> 01:14:47,419
你在這塈韟野
You're too valuable here.

1084
01:14:49,671 --> 01:14:53,634
- 這堣w沒什麼讓我做的，看來我只能… - 好吧，你可以去芝加哥
-There's nothing left for me to do-- -All right, you can go to Chicago.

1085
01:14:53,717 --> 01:14:54,968
謝謝你
Thank you.

1086
01:14:56,053 --> 01:14:58,597
看來我還是設法喝醉為妙
I guess I'd better try to get drunk anyway.

1087
01:15:00,307 --> 01:15:02,809
不過我警告你，你不會喜歡芝加哥的
I warn you, Jedediah, you won't like Chicago.

1088
01:15:02,851 --> 01:15:07,481
從湖上吹來的風可不小 而且他們很可能從未聽說過山珍海味
The wind comes off the lake, and they've probably never heard of Lobster Newburg.

1089
01:15:07,564 --> 01:15:09,775
下一個星期六，好嗎？
Will Saturday after next be all right?

1090
01:15:09,858 --> 01:15:11,818
- 隨你決定 - 謝謝
-Anytime you say. -Thank you.

1091
01:15:17,532 --> 01:15:22,496
為我的規則幹一杯，任何人都只知道?
A toast to love on my terms. Those are the only terms anybody knows:

1092
01:15:24,122 --> 01:15:25,332
他自己的規則
His own.

1093
01:15:38,261 --> 01:15:40,806
凱恩先生，我是《問事報》的
Mr. Kane, I'm from the Inquirer.

1094
01:15:50,065 --> 01:15:52,985
- 什麼事，年青人？ - 你還會從政嗎？
-What's that, young man? -Are you through with politics?

1095
01:15:53,068 --> 01:15:55,779
我會從政？我要說的剛好相反
Am I through with politics? I would say vice versa.

1096
01:15:57,155 --> 01:15:58,865
我們要做歌劇明星
We're going to be an opera star.

1097
01:15:58,907 --> 01:16:00,784
你將在大都會劇院表演嗎，凱恩太太？
Are you singing at the Metropolitan?

1098
01:16:00,867 --> 01:16:02,244
當然啦
We certainly are.

1099
01:16:02,411 --> 01:16:05,289
查利說，如果我不在那媞t唱 他就為我造一座歌劇院
Charlie said if I didn't, he'd build me an opera house.

1100
01:16:05,372 --> 01:16:06,873
看來並不需要
That won't be necessary.

1101
01:16:11,753 --> 01:16:15,048
不，不！
No, no, no!

1102
01:16:48,624 --> 01:16:50,125
--
Places, please!

1103
01:17:39,216 --> 01:17:42,010
李蘭先生是從戲劇的角度來寫的？
Mr. Leland is writing it from the dramatic angle?

1104
01:17:42,094 --> 01:17:45,555
- 我們還從新聞消息的角度報導了 - 還有社交的角度
-And we've covered it from the news end. -And the social.

1105
01:17:46,431 --> 01:17:48,642
音樂的評論怎樣？送來了嗎？
How about the music notice?

1106
01:17:48,684 --> 01:17:50,686
是的，已經在排版了
Yes, it's already made up.

1107
01:17:50,769 --> 01:17:53,438
墨爾文先生寫了一篇漂亮的評論
Mr. Mowan wrote a swell review.

1108
01:17:54,982 --> 01:17:59,152
- 熱情洋溢嗎？ - 是的，先生
-Enthusiastic? -Yes, sir.

1109
01:17:59,278 --> 01:18:01,905
- 伯恩斯坦先生 - 凱恩先生，真沒料到您的光臨！
Mr. Kane. This is a surprise.

1110
01:18:04,491 --> 01:18:06,493
我們準備發兩版的劇照
We've got two spreads of pictures.

1111
01:18:06,535 --> 01:18:08,412
音樂的評論是在頭版嗎？
The music notice on the front page?

1112
01:18:08,495 --> 01:18:12,165
但是還有一篇稿子沒到，劇評稿子
But there's still one notice to come. The dramatic.

1113
01:18:13,292 --> 01:18:14,835
劇評稿子
The dramatic notice.

1114
01:18:16,003 --> 01:18:20,549
